gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput

Class LISSStationServer

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • gov.usgs.anss.edgeoutput.LISSStationServer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public final class LISSStationServer
extends java.lang.Thread
    LISSStationServer.java - This controls the queue for one station for LISS output from the ChannelInfrastructure. It keeps the ring in memory so that it can be used by LISSOutputers which service a LISSSocket. Its thread listens for connections to the assigned port and creates a LISSSocket for each incoming connection. There is logic which should be called periodically from another thread which will prune off dead connections. Created on March 29, 2007, 5:22 PM
